76561198006639211,Recommended,239250,13927187,"Posted: 10 January, 2015",all,Waikiki,"Eu sunt Dracul!After I was highly disapointed by the console port of Lords of Shadows 1 I must say I really like this game. It got a 58 Metacritics score, but since I'm a sucker for Metroidvania and God of War-like games I gave it a try.And boy am I glad I gave it a chance. I have to admit the game needs some time to get you. The first two hours are kind of lame (The fight against the angelic robot and the boring sneaking part). But after the tutorial and the first visit to the science facility the game unfolds its beauty.The artdesign is fabulous, overall graphics, shadows and lightning are fantastic. Even more important, the controls are smooth even for a non gamepad-player like me. Combat is challenging throughout the game. After unlocking more and more combat options the normal fights as well as the boss fights are immensely fun to play (The whole toymaker part is a lesson in gamedesign for other devs). You can adjust the camera by mouse so there are no more fixed angles and even jumping is fun again. No more QTE, thank you for that dear devs.The game is kind of an open world game, you can constantly roam your castle and the modern world and unlock secret after secret while advancing through the game.The speakers and the music are nearly over the top. The speakers are so good and the music fits so fantasticly well it's scary.And last but not least this game is dark, no emo vampire he's the kind of vampire I want to watch in movies or play as in a game.My rating would be a 86 (edited), it's one of the best games of this kind I ever played.So give it a try and don't let yourself get fooled by the not so brilliant beginning."
