,Not Recommended,239250,32820884,Posted: 26 June,all,FreeToaster,"While I will play this game to completion and end up spending around 50-80 hours playing, I can't recommend the game.There are way too many little issues that have made what could have been a great game into one filled with annoyance.The game isnt hard. The combat isnt hard. Even on Prince of Darkness difficulty most bosses can be beaten by an attack/dodge routine, there are just certain moves that can 2 shot you now.The problem with combat is the fact that the parry move is largely unused as every mob from the smallest grunt to the final boss spams unblockable attacks, where in the previous game you were rewarded for having the skill to parry, here you rarely get the chance because 9/10 attacks are unblockable and unable to be parried. This doesnt make the combat harder, as you just spend more time dodging out of the way, but with those unblockable attacks comes with it an annoying sound to let you know an unblockable attack is coming and you will hear this sound every few seconds during combat at least, but often in succession until the last mob is dead for the entire game. The entire game.Maybe this is different on easier difficulties, but i'll never know. If it is, making mobs have 9/10 attacks be unblockable didnt make the game harder for me, just incredibly annoying.The shielded Vampire mobs also have an incredibly high pitched sound they will spam if you are not in their line of sight, It's so bad it makes me wonder if the devs wanted to annoy the players on purpose.  Then I remember there is a cutscene for restarting a checkpoint or dying and I have to assume that yes, that was their goal.The challenge arena will never start you off with full health, it will leave you at whatever you were at during the previous challenge or when you entered the arena. This means if you want to do more than one challenege you need to go back to the castle, leave the shop use an item to heal yourself, renter the shop purchase another healing item if needed reenter the arena and pick your challenge. During this process you will have to watch or cancel out about 6 small cutscenes. That is crazy. ""cinematic"" can be a good thing depending on the game, here it's a disease.As for the story of the game, it's not great, or at the very least it's told poorly. some elements are never explained and are extremely confusing when you first experience them and what I imagine was meant to be a twist or at least a surprise was pretty much obvious from the start.Say whatever you want about the first LOS not being Castlevania enough, it didnt have forced stealth sections and demons with shotguns, grenade launchers, and automatic weapons. I dont know how a team of people sat down and agreed that what Castlevania was missing was a modern day setting with guns and mechs. Maybe someday we'll get a MGS game set in 1700'sIt's not terrible, if you can look past the mountain of little annoyances it's an ok game, but for me those annoyances are too constant for me to suggest anyone else deal with them."
