,Recommended,239250,31227285,Posted: 18 April,all,Murderlol,"To be honest I don't really understand the hate this game got when it first came out. Having played both Lords of Shadow games I can say without a doubt that the first is better, but the second is still a great game in its own right. Great controls, well optimized with a perfect game length and plenty of exploration and replayability, it's a game where you'll get your money's worth. The combat is a little better than the first game, being similar to other 3rd person action games like God of War. The story isn't quite as good as the first because I think the character progression of Gabriel is what really made that story great, but it isn't bad here either. The level design overall is nice and the music is decent. My only real complaints are that some of the puzzles seemed unnecessary and the stealth bits were somewhat annoying, although infrequent and easy enough that I didn't care all that much. Overall it's a pretty solid action game that's worth a play especially for fans of the series and there's not much bad to say about it.The Revelations DLC is decent, I'd say it's maybe slightly better than the DLC from the first game. It's about 2-3 hours long and lets you play as a different character with a new weapon and different abilities in a story that takes place just before the start of LoS2 and explains a few events leading up to it. It's really not a necessary DLC story-wise but it's decently fun in its own right."
