 either a glowy thing waiting for you or a char shouting to you with explanations. Yet, some parts you just havent the foggiest bit of a hint of where to go.Low replay value. There are elements present to keep you busy after the main story is over, however I can't see entertainment value lasting with that; or starting a new save; albite there are always diffrent difficulty levels if you're into that.The only way to die in this game is in a giant explosion of blood. The enemies almost always blow up, or burst into blood. I think that greatly takes away from the feel of it.Another game that likes to kill off just about everyone. You catch onto the trend of: Oh a new guy. Guess he's the next boss..but this ones my opinion, maybe you just like all that murder.One list seems to be bigger than the other. Hrm.So to wrap up, The game has a solid foundation, and is fun; 15 ish+ hours gameplay. However there are some problems that sound like somebody put money over quality. I may have been nitpicking but this is a $60.00 game, and theres another $10.00 or so worth of DLC.Nothing is perfect, but if you're going to put somthing out at full price don't do it half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ Regrettably, that seems to be what this is. They came so close but just didn't go all the way.As I said up top; Sure I'll recomend this title.. but not right now. This is somthing that you will enjoy playing, but not with the current pricetag/greavences.P.S.Is it just me or do the DLC costumes just look like a recolored version of what he's already wearing??"
