cula simply stabs santan with the vampire killer or his combat cross, and then we get some vague dialouge between dracula and alucard, and then we get some awesome ending score to playt them off and the end. It just left a bad taste the mouth, an unstatsifying taste, that could have been better.(end of spoilers)Back to combat and battle a feel that the titans where neccasary , in the first game defeating the titan provided a feeling of gradure to the character, i made gaberial seem more than a man, something i didnt get from this game, i felt like the ""good"" gaberial was and is stronger than dracula(another spoiler) a part i thought was really cool was your battle with victor, it was like dracula was fighting his old self which was awesome but something they could have expanded upon more story wiseAnd that brings us to the story, long story short (haha thank you thank you ill be here all week), the story sucked so bad for me it was the fact that the first story was so good that i expected something even better my expectations were high and for good reason, yet the story not only fell short of expectations, but alot of others.I feel that they could have expanded upon so much, like dracula's stuggle with his own castle, dracula and his in self , they could have made not only fight his inner self but also his actual past self, and for that matter they could have made him fight all the people he killed in the first game like cornell, pan, the girl with the guardian titan, and so on. they could have added a little more to victors story and gave more purpose and so on.I could go on with the shouldve couldve games but we would be here all dayso in the end the game for me was good but not GREAT!!! and thats my problem is with the game that it could have been so much better, i know usually sequals arent as good as the orginal but thats a norm we cant accept everytime a game comes out it should be better then the last one, and for me Lords of Shadow 2 barely misses the mark