76561198006019148,Recommended,239250,9604083,"Posted: 23 March, 2014",all,Mike_Charger,"As the sequel to Castlevania: Lords of Shadow, one of the most memorable games of 2010 I played. This game holds up very well and takes advantage of the modern setting it takes place in pretty well.That said, it does have flaws, but the main thing is you are not getting a buggy game. I found no bugs, glitches, or problems while playing.The stealth elements could have been handled better, considering Konami funded this you would think they have *someone* who knows a thing or two about that.But for what it is worth, the few instances of stealth were handled better than I thought they could have been. I did not find myself confused too easily by some of the stealth sections. But they were, at first, problematic due to the fact that they seemed forced rather than a natural progression of things.That aside the artwork for the game is awesome, yes, the modern city sections of Castlevania seem out of place. But that is not a flaw to me. Dracula's castle is not Castlevania. The city which is named as such, was built on and around Dracula's castle. So the design changes from running around a beautiful old castle and its environments. To an open city that looks nice, but is not as nice as the castle, is not such a bad thing.I am not going to obsess over art direction when I want a game's story to make sense. And the story only makes complete sense once you are near the end of the game. At first I thought it was poor writing. But I suspect it was a bit of Play Mirror of Fate to get the full story/purchase our DLC.Yes, I honestly feel that with the announcement of DLC. I think they *may* have cut story content just for the DLC. But everything comes together towards the end of the main game anyway.The bosses are fun, the exploration is fun, generally speaking if you are on the fence about this and you played the original. You will LIKE the sequel. I personally love it, and love the way the game came together in the end in my opinion."
