76561198067590894,Recommended,239250,9284984,"Posted: 27 February, 2014",all,AxesoftheVoid,"A definite improvement over the last game.  Better world, story, and gameplay.The explorable world with collectable lore was a major plus. Exploration and secrets were a fairly good distraction that led me to look at the world a little more thoroughly. The lack of any side missions or story was a bit dissappointing.The story is fairly engaging, more so I imagine considering I played the first game and have already developed an understanding and sympathetic realtionship with the main character.   Robert Carlyle offered a wonderful dracula and the supporting cast were almost invariably superb.  I'm glad they had the lore portion of the in game menu, because without it I would have felt that they introduced some characters out of the blue without any exposition. Which could be viewed as lazy but I didn't find it too offensive.The combat is quite fluid and the controls are pretty intuitive.  It only took me about ten minutes to get a really good grasp on the mechanics of the game.The boss fights are pretty good as well.  One complaint about the boss fights is that they seem to be very interesting and tactically stressful to begin with but they gradually push into tedium when you learn what tactics are necessary to defeat them.  This is most prevenlant in the first boss and last two bosses.  Another negative thing about certain sections of the game would be the ""stealth"" sections.  They were lacluster, slowing the game down unecessarily sometimes, mostly due to the whole system seeming under-developed.Overall this game has alot to offer in most of its areas with only a few minor misses but doesn't really do anything epicly well or ground breaking.  I definitely enjoyed it."
