76561198024599399,Recommended,239250,12234900,"Posted: 25 September, 2014",all,Baron,"This game gets a 6.5/10 - but the revelations DLC gets 8/10If you love vampires (the kind that don't sparkle) then there is really no way to exclude this from your collection, because  when it comes down to it, this is a high budget vampire action game. Whips, swords, claws, and excellent cinematography within the world. Its the first vampire game I've ever played where you truly feel like an immortal being, and time passes in an almost dreamlike way. I personally loved the the parts of the game (about half) spent inside Dracula's Castle, especially walking outside amongst the frozen ramparts with those beautiful gothic spires in the distance, fighting Knights and such. (The whole time not entirely sure whether this castle is an actual place, or it was destroyed and you are simplying battling through your mind palace to reclaim lost memories) If thats the sort of thing that appeals to you, then this game is worth every penny.The other half of the game is set inside a futuristic post apocalyptic earth; it feels kind of like you're playing a dungeon in ""The Secret World"" - not badly done, just a strange break of character to fight flying riot police with machine guns after fighting knights in a castle.The reason I rate this game, especially the original, so low, is because the story and character progression feels like a PS2 game. It is extremely linear; there is very little in the way of character customization or side storylines. The other reason, and this is the main reason, is that the instructions are often very vague and have only one very specific trigger to complete an objective, so you often spend time puzzle solving something relatively mundane. I personally had to look up how to do a lot of things, and it was frustrating. There is also a lot of climbing in the first one for some reason. About 20% of the game feels like a Guild Wars 2 jumping puzzle or an Assassin's Creed exploration mission. Revelations adds a couple of mechanics to shorten this process, but it can still be annoying.End result is, the more you like vampires, the more you will like this game."
