76561198111053538,Recommended,239250,9658446,"Posted: 28 March, 2014",all,xbigvmanx,"I loved the first Castlevania LoS. I was really excited the moment they shown the first trailer for the sequal over two years ago that I was highly anticipating this next installment.  When the reviews started coming out for the sequal I was upset what they were saying when I had high hopes for this game.  The negative comments seem to over embelish the quality of the game that it would get a D minus rating over issues such as the stealth portion, a shallow ending, and boring environments.  After playing this game I thought whoever was playing this game seem to be as bad as the critics, reviewing movies in that they are blind to what is an actual great movie when the majority movie going public seems to love the movie.  This game my fellow gamers is a great quality game.  Gone the fixed camera angels, you now have a free camera you can manipulate around the character to get a better view of Dracula and his environment.  The environment is breathtaking, The amount of work and detail that went into Dracula's castle and Castlevania City makes you take a moment to study the detail and architecture. The environment also reminds me they were trying a Castlevania SOTN where the city and castle are connected to each other. The gameplay is very smooth especially the combat portion. Gone are the Combat Cross, light and shadow magic systems in place are the Shadow Whip, Void Sword, and Chaos Claws.  My favorite weapon is Chaos Claws simply because it reminds me of using Hercules Gauntlets in God of War.  But interchanging between weapons is a fluid motion you can make awesome combos.  If I had to make any complaints about this game is the story.  It didn't feel fulfilling (ie character development)  especially the end.    I was disappointed with the last boss Satan. It would have been nice to fight him head on vice using (SPOILER ALERT) someone close to Dracula. Also I wish the ending had an epilogue like the first one. It sort of left a question mark on Dracula's fate.  Like I said the grips that people had of this game is minor.  The stealth system was interesting idea but in some place poorly executed. Like when Dracula is already powerful why does he need to avoid Satan's Elite Armored brutes? Some of the stealth puzzles can prove irritating for some people have to start over and over again namely sneaking past Pan's brother.  But after observing other players in how they pass him it became quite easy and a little scarey lol.  This is great game which I highly recommend if your fan of this genre or God Of War type games.  Additionally I am re-playing this game again. This is one of those games I hope they make a movie out of this game use this plot for the story."
,Recommended,239250,14514936,"Posted: 17 February, 2015",all,Bax,"I really enjoyed this game. I played 1st one as well so I was interested in how the story ends especially because of amazing outro. The story of previous game was amazing with a lot of plot twists. However, in case of this game, it was shorter and narrower. Anyway, I still enjoyed it and I really loved the ending. If I would play it as a standalone game I would be still satisfied, but I also understand those who are disappointed especially when they are comparing it to the first game.When it comes to gameplay - play this game with controller!!! (I played with X-box controller and I can only recommend it). There was like only one mini game when I switched to mouse for a faster and smoother aiming. Otherwise this game is really difficult to play with keyboard, especially because hints are given in X-box controller binding (for example ""Press [insert green circle with A letter] to continue"").Combat system was amazing compared to the previous game. Camera was also improved. Those two things let you really enjoy all the fights, especially those with bosses. On the other hand, difficulty was decreased (at least this is my impression) compared to the previous game. And not only during fights. I also found climbing passages much easier. Yes, they were smoother, more intuitive and much less painful than in previous game, but on the other hand, I felt like I am just moving stick in one of the 4 directions and Gabriel is auto-piloting himself through those catch points on the wall. If those passages are replaced with cinematics of Gabriel climbing some wall, I would not see any difference and that is a bit disappointing for me.When it comes to stealth passages, I see a lot of people did not like them. Honestly, I expected those passages will be very often and very boring after reading some reviews, but I found them quite interesting and there were actually only few in the game.Another thing I would like to mention are puzzles. I really liked puzzles in the first game and this was probably the biggest disappointment for me, because there were only few puzzles and difficulty of all of them was like difficulty of puzzles in pre-school kid magazines.And last thing I would like to talk about are graphics. They are really amazing. Especially castle is truly master piece. However, it is looking quite the same all the time. During playing the first game, player is going through various environments. Each one looks different. Each one got different colour scheme. Each one got unique textures. Environments in first game are truly amazing and I still remember a lot of amazing sceneries from there. But with this game everything is dark and quite the same. Only colourful place I can remember was one garden passage within the castle (I will not say more details to not spoil it). Details are still really amazing, but everything is so dark and similar, that you will stop sense them.I guess this is mainly because the game is open-world like and not level system like in previous game so environment have to be ""one solid connected piece"". In the first game all what was needed was simple introduction ""and in this level Gabriel went to some other place far away from previous one"" and environment could change drastically. In this game it has to fit all together, because there is no space for long distance travelling.Well, to sum it up - I was satisfied with this game. If I would not play the first one I would probably enjoy it much more. The truth is, that the first game set really high standards and they were overcome only in a very few cases. For the most of them, they were below those from the first game. Still, I would give this game something about 70-80%."
