76561197970474192,Recommended,239250,13218998,"Posted: 3 December, 2014",all,jmpreston,"I'll give C:LoS2 a limited ""thumbs-up,"" but based almost entirely only the outstanding visuals, audio, and effects. To be brief, the models, animations, textures, lighting effects are simply superb. I would often walk into new environments and just pan the camera around to take it all in. The craftsmanship of the content is what propelled me towards the end.However, my big concern with this game is that I was hoping for a different mix of ingredients. In most action/adventures games (God of War, Batman: Arkham series) there is a nice mixture of combat, exploration, puzzle solving, and traversal (climbing, swimming, grappling, etc.) What I wanted from Lord of Shadow 2 was 50% combat and 50% everything else. What I got was basically 15% combat with a TON of emphasis on uninspried puzzles, boring traversal, and some rather obvious exploraiton. There were many, many times in the game when I would walk down a hallway and wish I would be jumped by a bad guy just so I could use my weapons.In the end, I still played and enjoyed it. But I wished for a lot more combat and a lot less of everything else."
