76561198128822447,Recommended,239250,10780282,"Posted: 24 June, 2014",all,UNBELIEVABLY GAY,"This game is almost the perfect balance of right and wrong game design.The Good: The hack and slash gameplay is incredibly fun. The leveling system for your weapons actually requires you to try out different combos in order to max out and get points to make the weapon stronger, which encourages trying new attack patterns and not using the same, one effective combo over and over again (*cough* God of War *cough*). The character models are very detailed and the voice acting is pretty spot on. Not to mention the level design is absolutely gorgeous when you're in the castle. The bosses have memorable designs and battles. And I loved the open world to explore that wasn't of the MetroidVania design.The Bad: Despite the game throwing hordes of different looking enemies at you, they oddly enough don't feel too varied. The game constantly shifts back and forth betwen the modern city evironment and Dracula's castle, but it feels kinda hectic and you almost never do anything in the city; Kinda like they just didn't have much planned out for it. The story is actually pretty awful and does an almost complete nose dive in the last hour or so and ends with one of the weakest plot resolutions I think I've seen in a long time, even though everything up to that point in the writing feels pretty sturdy; Almost as if the writer just stopped caring when the game was almost finished. And the stealth sections are absolutely terrible. They're the kind where you only have ONE way to go about getting through each section and it never changes EVER. The game designed one specific enemy for you to encounter during this sections which kill you easily. This is explained by Zobek saying you're too weak to fight them. If you're familiar with old vampire lore, you know they can take different animal shapes, typically being of the night time variety (wolves, bats, etc.) but the game only lets you change into one animal, being rats. But both these points really fall through at the end when you're pretty much a full strength Dracula and you're still having to sneak past these things disguised as rats.I don't really know if I'd recomend this or not. I mean, I did enjoy the game for the most part. But if you're wanting to play this because you enjoyed the last one as I did and really wanted to see how things would end for Gabriel, all I can say is, without giving any spoilers, I couldn't have felt like I got a bigger slap in the face. But if you don't care about the story and want to play a beautiful game with some of the best hack and slash I've seen in a while, I say try.EDIT: I decided to give this game a recommendation because despite its flaws it was one of the better games of 2014. I suppose that's some merit"
