76561198041756601,Recommended,239250,22119896,"Posted: 29 March, 2016",all,JiiPee,"Shortly: (trying no to tell any spoilers and and I didn't play the DLC: Revelations)Basically, the game is a sequel for the original Castlevania: Lords of Shadow and the Castlevania: Mirror of Fate games, and it continues the story of Dracula (Gabriel Belmont) thousand years after the events of those 2 games.The game is staged on a modern era, where Satan is once again trying to destroy the world of men with the help of his Acolytes.Unlike in the original LoS game, this time the game is a openworld game, however you can only travel to new areas AFTER you've aquired a certain powerup to access them. And like in all openworld games, this one also has fast-travel system, but its pretty primitive.There are 2 different worlds that you can travel, the modern era where the Satan's forcers brings havoc and the Dracula's Castle where the Dracula's own blood is trying to trap you.Graphics are decent, sounds and voice actings are doreable. The battle system is slightly better than it was in the original LoS, but at the same time it feels a little bit watered down from what it was.The overall story is a cliche, because you can easily predict that what's about to happen. However, it is interesting enough to see it through. The ending itself however was a disappointment for me, because there's no conclusion, but that's just my opinion.Pros:+ Battle and upgrade systems+ Boss encounters (though the last boss was disappointment)+ Lots of different enemies+ Lots of collectables for those interested+ Over 20 hours of gameplay if you collect every collectable like I didCons:- Disappointing last boss- Awful Fast-travel system (though you only need it when you're searching for collectables)- Lots of annoying enemies at the end- Bad ending (there's no conclusion in my opinion but then again I didn't play the revelations DLC)- The Shop's location is bad, because getting some of the collectables requires a certain item that can only be bought from the shop, so you need to visit it a lot- Kleido's Challenges offer no reward except a few Steam achievements- Few un-skippable cutscenes and events such as the slow paced transition between the modern era - Dracula's CastleDo I recommend ?:If you're interested to see what happens to the Dracula after the events of Lords of Shadow and Mirror of Fate, then this might interest you. But if you haven't played those 2 games before, don't care about the story and are only interested for the action, then don't bother.Verdict: 6 / 10 - Slightly good game( 1 = Do-not-bother game5 = Average game10 = Must own game )"
