,Recommended,239250,12216551,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,SilentWanderer,"Dont believe the metacritic review score, decide for yourself. This is a beautifully crafted game with a fun and intuitive combat system. The controls are far tighter than LoS 1 so you have more room for precise dodging. The story jumps a bit and is certainly lacking in some areas but there are no more plot holes in this than in LoS 1. If you listen to the story you may even start feeling emotional in parts.As the game progresses and recover more abilities it makes you start to feel alot more powerful though not too powerful as to make the game feel too easy.However it is not all good in this game obviously. Enemy AI can be horribly broken sometimes and its not always obvious how to eascape a situation when hit by an unblockable attack. Button mashing is prevelant and not always in a good way though the quicktime events are suitably entertaining. The game has a way of ALWAYS giving some enemies an unfair advantage, some of which you can't counter until later in the game. But going back to these areas after playing more of that game allows you to access previously inaccessible areas.Graphically the game is amazing with the castle sections being much, MUCH better than the city. It does make you wish the impending apocalypse would hold of for a bit though so you could truely strike terror into the people of the modern day as DRACULA PRINCE OF DARKNESS! *ahem*overall 8/10 I would say definately worth it if you liked the first LoS, are interested in Gabriel's story and prefer faster paced action, while still having to think on your feet."
