76561198203073683,Recommended,239250,29305500,Posted: 16 January,all,lukehampton04,"I've been playing Castlevania since the first NES version, and I must say that I am really impressed with this as the conclusion of Lords of Shadow 1 and Mirror of Fate. The graphics (mostly in the architecture) and music are fanstastic. The stealth parts didn't bother me as much as everyone else.I would say the biggest con in this game is that the enemies are all relatively the same strength and kind of boring. I think it would have been a little more fun to whip my way through barrages of weaker skeletons and zombies with stronger enemies dispersed strategically through each area. As it is now, pretty much every enemy takes quite a few whips and combos to defeat -- none of them are particularly challenging, but rather time consuming.Ultimately, I did enjoy this game and would definitely recommend this and the other 'newer' series to any Castlevania fan."
